## Layers — non-negotiable shape

```
HTTP request
    → index.php (Router) + AuthGate (session UI only)
    → Controller (orchestration: read $_GET/$_POST, validate, delegate, include view)
    → Service / Fetcher / RefreshAllService (no SQL; I/O and business logic)
    → Repository (**only place raw SQL lives** for DB access)
    → PDO (local) — entry-source reads may qualify table names via entryTable()
Views / formatters: escape (e() / htmlspecialchars), local time for display only
```

- **Plugins** (`src/Plugin/<Name>/`): implement `SourceFetcherInterface`; **no SQL**, no globals; may throw; `RefreshAllService` catches and logs.
- **Repositories** (`src/Repository/`): return **raw** arrays/DTOs — **no** `htmlspecialchars`, no presentation.
- **Controllers** (`src/Controller/`): **no SQL**; thin orchestration.

## Satellite / mothership — entry vs local tables

- **Entry-source data** (feeds, feed_items, emails, lex_items, calendar_events, sender_tags, …): reads in repositories **must** use `entryTable()` / `entryDbSchemaExpr()` where applicable so satellites read the mothership DB. See `magnitu-integration.mdc` and `bootstrap.php`.
- **Always local** (never `entryTable()`): `entry_scores`, `system_config`, `magnitu_labels`, `plugin_run_log`, `entry_favourites`, plugin sidecars.
- **Writes** to entry tables from satellites: forbidden; runners short-circuit; repos may throw if satellite (defence in depth).

When adding a **new** entry-family table: decide if it is mothership-owned entry data (use `entryTable()` in the owning repo only) or instance-local (no wrapper).

## Bounded queries and time

- Every list-returning repository method takes **`$limit` and `$offset`** with a hard cap (see `EntryRepository::MAX_LIMIT` pattern in `core-plugin-architecture.mdc`).
- **UTC** everywhere below the view: `bootstrap.php` + DB session timezone; `DateTimeImmutable` with explicit UTC in repos; views/formatters may convert to `SEISMO_VIEW_TIMEZONE` for display.

## Configuration

- **Instance / app keys**: `system_config` (not ad-hoc JSON files for new features unless the slice explicitly introduces a file).
- **Plugin blocks**: `plugin:<identifier>` rows; **shared** filters that are not a plugin block may use another agreed prefix (e.g. `lex:…`) — see Slice 5a patterns in `README-REORG.md`.
- **Secrets**: `config.local.php` only (never commit); use `.example` for shape.

## HTTP surface — how to add routes

1. Register in `index.php` on `Router`: action string → `Class::method`, read-only flag as appropriate.
2. **Session-protected UI**: not on `AuthGate` public whitelist unless it is `health`, `login`, `logout`, `migrate`, or `magnitu_*` / `export_*` (Bearer-only inside controller).
3. **Mutating POST** from the browser: **CSRF** (`CsrfToken::field()` + `verifyRequest()`). **Magnitu v3** / `export_*` use Bearer tokens — no CSRF.
4. **Links and redirects**: `getBasePath()` — no hardcoded host/path for app URLs.

If `CsrfToken::field()` is rendered on a GET page, add the action to `Router::READONLY_KEEP_SESSION_FOR_CSRF` (see comment in `src/Http/Router.php`) so flash messages are not lost.

## New data sources

| Kind | Where it goes |
|------|----------------|
| Third-party API that breaks occasionally | **New plugin** under `src/Plugin/<Name>/` + one line in `PluginRegistry` (no filesystem scanning). |
| RSS, mail, scraper (core-owned) | **Core** fetcher/service + existing family repo; follow `RefreshAllService` / `CoreRunner` patterns. |
| Swiss Parliament Medien / “Parl MM” press lists | **Core** `ParlPressFetchService` (`core:parl_press`) → **`feed_items`** via `feeds.source_type = parl_press`. **Not** Lex, **not** Leg, **no** new table — see `core-plugin-architecture.mdc`. |
| New “family” of stored entries | Extend the **appropriate family table** (`lex_items`, `calendar_events`, …) via repository `upsertBatch` + plugin DTOs — **no** per-plugin tables unless a slice explicitly adds a sidecar table (see `core-plugin-architecture.mdc`). |

## Magnitu v3 and machine exports

- Do **not** change JSON shapes or `entry_type` strings without coordinating **Magnitu v3** (`sync.py` / `main.py`) and docs in `magnitu-integration.mdc`.
- **Leg (`calendar_event`)** is included in **Magnitu v3** and export APIs — see `calendar-events.mdc`.

## Schema and migrations

- **No** DDL on arbitrary requests. New tables/columns → **numbered migration** in `src/Migration/`, runner in `MigrationRunner.php`, append to `docs/db-schema.sql` as required by the project.
- After schema changes, document deploy/test steps per `webspace-testing.mdc`.

## Consolidation process (numbered slices)

- **Scope** lives in `docs/consolidation-plan.md`. Do not expand scope mid-slice; use `slice-scope-fidelity.mdc`.
- **Migration log**: append **`README-REORG.md`** when a slice ships (newest section on top) — paths, not line numbers.
- **README.md**: final polish at end of consolidation; do not bloat it slice-by-slice (`documentation-strategy.mdc`).
- **In-app about**: user-facing, only when features stabilise.
- **Slice done**: run **Gemini spot-check** handoff from `gemini-spot-check.mdc` before treating the next slice as started.

## Quick checklist before opening a PR / uploading

- [ ] No SQL outside `src/Repository/` (except migrations).
- [ ] Entry tables use `entryTable()` in repos; scoring/config local.
- [ ] Lists bounded; exports respect caps.
- [ ] No HTML in repository return values.
- [ ] Internal URLs use `getBasePath()`.
- [ ] New mutating POSTs have CSRF when under session auth.
- [ ] UTC below views; ISO output with `Z` / offset where applicable.
- [ ] Cron and web refresh share the same pipeline when the feature is part of “full refresh” (`deployment-portability.mdc`).

## Anti-patterns (do not introduce)

- New templating engine / heavy framework “for one feature”.
- Hardcoded `https://` or install path in PHP views/controllers (except documented env like `SEISMO_MOTHERSHIP_URL`).
- Unbounded `SELECT *` list endpoints.
- Circuit-breaking plugins silently — use logs + diagnostics (`core-plugin-architecture.mdc`).
- **Per-module admin UI under `Settings`.** Feeds, Scraper, and Mail management belong on the module's own page via an `Items | <thing>` toggle (0.4.4 "Module-owned management UI" pattern). `Settings` is strictly for global app state (**Magnitu v3** keys/preferences, Retention, UI defaults). See `docs/consolidation-plan.md` Slice 8.
- **New code built around `sender_tags`.** `sender_tags` is the pre-0.4.3 legacy data model. First-class mail admin targets **`email_subscriptions`** (domain-first matching `@example.com`, `show_in_magnitu` flag, one-click unsubscribe). Dashboard filter pills still read `sender_tags` for backwards-compat, but any new UI or repository goes against `email_subscriptions`.
- **Setup wizard that assumes `file_put_contents()` will succeed.** On shared hosts the PHP user often can't write to the install directory. The wizard must `is_writable()`-check and seamlessly degrade to a copy-paste UI that generates the `config.local.php` block for the admin to paste via File Manager / SFTP. Never `chmod 0777`, never fall back to `/tmp`, never silently skip a config write. See `docs/consolidation-plan.md` Slice 9.
- **Silently dropping a 0.4 feature from the URL surface.** If a route retires (e.g. `ai_view`), the in-app About page and/or `README.md` must explicitly name the replacement (e.g. the Slice 5 export API) so users can follow the forwarding pointer. Silent deletion is a support-ticket generator.
